Magic Story Round-Up:
First Half - Amonkhet ages ago. Bolas basically laid waste to the entire plane and Naktamun is the final remaining city. Gods are basically powerless against him. He shatters Kefnet's mind, and then kills EVERYONE except the children with a spell. 
Oketra and Hazoret try to run and save the children, but Bolas conquers. Cruel irony that Hazoret is the one who spears initiates as she is the most motherly of the gods. Bolas "stores" the missing three gods for later.

Current - Bolas hasn't shown up yet.
Mobs of crowds go to see the Gate to the Afterlife open. Everyone looking forward to it, it opens... and it's desert nothingness. Razaketh appears and turns the river to blood. Djeru's faith is wholly shaken, but he hasn't revolted against Bolas yet. Razaketh says Liliana can't hide from him.
It was a good story but Bolas' plan, whatever it is, feels way Dr. Evil at the moment
How so?
I guess we need to see what the end game is, but it just seems really over complicated

Isn't everything Bolas does that way? A few comments in the Reddit thread were interesting. One suggested that he used Amonkhet to store some of his pre-mending power or do something along those lines, i.e. "Rapidly losing omnipotence."

Well also get info on his relation with Razaketh later too (confirmed by Alison Luhrs)
Very true. They've never really paid off any of these far reaching schems of his though
Not to say they won't, but I get a Lost vibe from a lot of it where they concocted a cool beginning with no plan for an ending
I hope bolas takes out all the current gatewatch walkers.

Yea, they're probably slow-rolling intentionally because of how big and important he is as a villain. 

"I want to get my pre-Mending powers back." Is the big one, but we're not sure how he's doing that yet. I expect that we'll get some clarification of his end goal through his abuse of Amonkhet, and maybe some bread crumbs for his other schemes, but well likely see a big build-up to anything substantial. I'm fine with them taking their time with him, unlike how they handled Ulamog and Kozilek.
I want bolas to take out the current walker group, then ugin and sorin to avenge them. That way we get to see more of the walkers with some more depth to then.
Bolas is an OG walker. He'll hopefully be able to take them all out.
